# Illustrates the ".env must not contain tuning-only keys" contract rule
# (docs/pipeline-unification/configuration/env-contract.md's Design Rules:
# "`.env` does not contain normal pipeline tuning knobs"; config-schema.md's
# Drift Checks: "tuning-only key appears only in .env").
#
# NOT WIRED to a test (2026-07-12 alignment audit, bead axon_rust-ldozg): no
# env-schema validator exists in axon-core yet to reject this automatically.
# AXON_HYBRID_CANDIDATES is a real, currently-shipped tuning knob (see root
# CLAUDE.md's env var reference); the target contract wants it expressed as
# `[retrieval].hybrid-candidates` in config.toml instead (already supported —
# see crates/axon-core/tests/fixtures/config/full.valid.toml). Content-only
# fixture for now.
QDRANT_URL=http://127.0.0.1:53333
TEI_URL=http://127.0.0.1:52000
AXON_HYBRID_CANDIDATES=100
